<TITLE> BTRC invites views on IPTSP regulations </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 19 (bdnews24.com) - Bangladesh Telecommunications Regulatory Commission on Monday published the second draft regulations for Internet Protocol Telephony Service Provider (IPTSP) licences. "Once licensed, Internet Protocol Telephony Service Providers will be able provide customers with low-cost call rates inside and outside the country," BTRC chairman Maj Gen (retd) Monzurul Alam said. "IPTSP is an advanced technology, which can facilitate many value added services." "I believe internet penetration will also increase after providing IP Telephony licences to the ISPs." BTRC, in a press release, said any institution or individual can give their opinion on the draft regulations by Jan. 26. The regulations are available on BTRC's website. bdnews
